claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: A table comparing relative vaccine effectiveness (rVE) of Flublok versus standard-dose quadrivalent influenza vaccines (Afluria, Fluarix, FluLaval, SD Fluzone, and Flucelvax) across subgroups (overall, by sex, age groups, risk conditions, and seasons) with unadjusted and adjusted (%) rVE estimates and 95% confidence intervals. The table presents comparative effectiveness percentages and confidence intervals, not antigen content or immunogenicity data, and therefore does not support the claim regarding 3× HA antigen content of Flublok.
